The African National Congress (ANC) in KwaZulu-Natal has confirmed their regional conference which will take place from 3 to 5 April. The announcement was made following a meeting at Moses Mabhida Stadium between the secretary-general of the ANC, Ace Magashule and branch leaders on 9 February. Speaking to Tabloid Newspapers, Ricardo Mthembu, ANC provincial spokesperson said: “We got the go ahead from the secretary-general, Ace Magashule, for the regional conference to begin.” Mthembu said Magashule seemed to be impressed with the membership audit hence he gave them a green light for the conference. He added that the party’s branch general meetings are set to begin on 15 February. During a media briefing held at ANC provincial offices in Durban recently, Mdumisendi Ntuli, party provincial secretary said: “The office of the secretary general has signed the membership audit reports of eThekwini, Lower South Coast, General Gizenga Mpanza and Josia Gumede regions, paving a way for these regions to begin with branch general meetings in order to nominate delegates for their respective regional conferences.”